[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sheffield United 3-1 Bradford City

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sheffield United extended their unbeaten run to five games with a comfortable win over Bradford.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Billy Sharp opened the scoring for the Blades when he shot from the edge of the area into the bottom corner.
The lead was doubled when Bantams defender Stephen Darby could only turn Paul Coutts' cross into his own net.
Martyn Woolford headed a third for the hosts before Gary Liddle nodded in from a corner for a late consolation goal for Phil Parkinson's side.
